1. Remove duplicates from a list.

1st approach-->
-one of the most common set questions in Python.
   A set does not preserve the original order.
-  A set can never contain duplicate elements.
l=[1,2,3,4,6,2,1]
l=list(set(l))
print(l)
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)


2nd approach-->
Method 2: Using a Set While Preserving Order
l=[1,2,3,4,6,2,1]

seen=set()
res=[]
for i in l:
    if i not in seen:
        seen.add(i)
        res.append(i)
print(res)
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)
